		<div align="justify"><font face="arial" size="-1" color="#303030">Planned updates to the Innoruuk.Com Calendar:<BR><BR>- All bookings will soon be scheduled only in PST (Verant's time). I will try to include time conversion help as much as possible in the entry form. But this will prevent the overlaps that keep occuring. I will backup the database, and convert all future bookings to PST time - Please be aware of this impending change.<BR>- Updating a scheduled event will stop reverting the year back to 2000 in the select box. This has already been done, I've just removed 2000 as a choice.<BR>- Will update calendar to prevent any guild from booking more than 2 dates. With the conversion to PST, I can probably also system-restrict future events from violating the 1 weekday/1 weekend rule. Or at least issue a warning to users if they're about to violate the rule.<BR><BR>Thanks guys, I know a lot of these have been a long time coming, they'll be in there soon.<BR><BR>If you have any more reasonable suggestions, please leave a message under "Ask Innoruuk.Com". I'm only 1 programmer, so extensive applications/projects won't be possible. =/<BR><BR><BR>- Cymric</div><br>
			
